transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you for calling Viagra. How can I assist you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I've been trying to get a response back from somebody.

Speaker 1: I was looking for, do you have a text line that I've tried a few times,

Speaker 2: or I should say an email, sorry about that.

Speaker 1: And I get no response back about the order I received.

Speaker 2: What's your name and date of birth?

Speaker 1: My name is Tim Odom, O-D-O-M. Date of birth is 9-17-1957.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Okay, and what's your question, Tim, in regards to your order?

Speaker 2: Yeah, like I said in the email, the product did not work for me,

Speaker 1: so I was looking for a refund and send the rest back.

Speaker 2: That is strange, because I do see here that you are getting Viagra AGB,

Speaker 1: and that's the best that there is.

Speaker 2: Can you do me a favor?

Speaker 1: I just want to make sure that they didn't accidentally send you classic Viagra

Speaker 2: instead of the AGB.

Speaker 1: Do you have the pills with you?

Speaker 2: Well, it's not in my hand, but I'm going that way right now.

Speaker 1: Okay, what did you want to know?

Speaker 2: Okay, so take a look at the pills.

Speaker 1: The pills, do they have a number 50 engraved on them,

Speaker 2: or do they say something else?

Speaker 1: The pills?

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: The pills have a number 50?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: They don't say AC-340?

Speaker 2: No.

Speaker 1: Okay, well that is strange.

Speaker 2: Maybe you just need a higher strength.

Speaker 1: It does show here that you are taking 50 milligrams,

Speaker 2: so that could be the reason why it's not working for you.

Speaker 1: So what I can go ahead and do for you, Tim,

Speaker 2: is that I can send you 10 free pills of 100 milligrams for you to try

Speaker 1: and see if you notice a difference.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Okay, so I'll send you 10 free.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: And I'll be receiving it within the next three to five business days,

Speaker 2: okay?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Have a good rest of your day.

Speaker 2: Bye, Tim.

Speaker 1: Bye.

Speaker 2: Bye.
